## Encryption

### In agent/script context

```typescript
import { encryptUint64, encryptBatch } from "@fhevm/sdk";

// Single value
const { handles, inputProof } = await encryptUint64(
  2000_000000n,     // $2000 USDC (6 decimal places)
  vaultAddress,     // contract that will receive this
  userAddress       // wallet submitting the transaction
);

// Multiple values — one SDK call, one inputProof covers all
const { handles, inputProof } = await encryptBatch([
  { type: "uint64", value: collateralGwei },
  { type: "uint64", value: borrowAmountUsdc },
], vaultAddress, userAddress);
// handles[0] = collateral, handles[1] = borrow amount
```

### In frontend context

```typescript
import { useEncrypt } from "../hooks/useEncrypt";

const { encrypt, encrypting } = useEncrypt(CONTRACT_ADDRESS);
const encrypted = await encrypt("uint64", 42n);
// encrypted.handles[0] and encrypted.inputProof are Uint8Array
// Convert to hex before passing to writeContractAsync (see page.tsx)
```

**RULE:** The `inputProof` is bound to exactly one `contractAddress` + `userAddress` pair.
Never reuse a proof across different contracts. (FHEVM-005)

**RULE:** `handles` and `inputProof` are `Uint8Array`. When passing to Wagmi/ethers,
convert with `` `0x${Buffer.from(handles[0]).toString("hex")}` ``. (FHEVM-010)

---

## Submitting Encrypted Transactions

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — convert Uint8Array handles/proof to hex for Wagmi
await writeContractAsync({
  address: vaultAddress as `0x${string}`,
  abi:     VAULT_ABI,
  functionName: "borrow",
  args: [
    `0x${Buffer.from(handles[0]).toString("hex")}` as `0x${string}`,
    `0x${Buffer.from(inputProof).toString("hex")}` as `0x${string}`,
  ],
});

// ❌ Wrong — Uint8Array will be serialized incorrectly by Wagmi
await writeContractAsync({ args: [handles[0], inputProof] });
```

---

## Public Decryption

```typescript
import { publicDecrypt } from "@fhevm/sdk";

// ✅ CORRECT — returns { results, clearValues }
const { results, clearValues } = await publicDecrypt([handle]);
// clearValues[0] is the plaintext BigInt

// ❌ WRONG — abiEncodedClearValues and decryptionProof do not exist (FHEVM-007)
const { abiEncodedClearValues, decryptionProof } = await publicDecrypt([handle]);
```

---

## User Reencryption

### In frontend context (Wagmi)

```typescript
import { useReencrypt } from "../hooks/useReencrypt";

const { values, reveal, loading } = useReencrypt(contractAddress, userAddress);
// handle from getHandle() is bytes32 (string) — convert to BigInt
await reveal([BigInt(handle as string)]);
// values[0] is the decrypted plaintext BigInt
```

### In agent/script context

```typescript
import { reencryptBatch } from "@fhevm/sdk";

const [collateral, debt] = await reencryptBatch(
  [collateralHandle, debtHandle],
  vaultAddress,
  userAddress,
  {
    signTypedData: async (domain, types, message) =>
      signer.signTypedData(domain, types, message),
  }
);
```

