## Agent Runtime (No Browser Required)

Agents are headless scripts that interact with FHE contracts using a private key.

### 1. Agent Initialization
```typescript
import { FhevmAgent } from "./agent/fhevm-agent";

const agent = new FhevmAgent(
  process.env.SEPOLIA_RPC_URL!,
  process.env.AGENT_PRIVATE_KEY!,
  "sepolia"
);
```

### 2. Encryption for Agents
Agents use `agent.encryptUint64()` which performs encryption locally without a browser
provider, making them suitable for background tasks.

### 3. Monitoring Loops
```bash
npm run agent:monitor
```

---

## Contract Getter Rules

Handle values returned from Solidity are **`bytes32`** — always convert to `BigInt`
before passing to the SDK.

```solidity
// ✅ Correct — each concern gets its own getter, returns bytes32
function getHandle() external view returns (bytes32) {
    return euint64.unwrap(_number);
}

function getPositionHandles(address borrower)
    external view returns (bytes32 collateralHandle, bytes32 debtHandle)

// ❌ Wrong — bundled tuple causes off-by-one errors in TypeScript
function getPositionHandles(address borrower)
    external view returns (bytes32, bytes32, bytes32)
```

```typescript
// ✅ Named destructuring + BigInt conversion
const { collateralHandle, debtHandle } = await vault.getPositionHandles(borrower);
await reveal([BigInt(collateralHandle), BigInt(debtHandle)]);

// ❌ FHEVM-008 — breaks silently if return order changes
const handles = await vault.getPositionHandles(borrower);
const health  = handles[2]; // always undefined — only 2 values returned
```

---

## Solidity Rules for FHE.allow()

```solidity
// ✅ Always call both after creating/reassigning a euint
euint64 amount = FHE.fromExternal(encryptedInput, inputProof);
FHE.allowThis(amount);
FHE.allow(amount, msg.sender);

// ❌ Silent failure — handle is permanently unreadable
euint64 amount = FHE.fromExternal(encryptedInput, inputProof);
positions[msg.sender].debt = amount; // missing allowThis
```

---

## FHE Operations Cannot Be `view` or `pure`

```solidity
// ❌ Wrong
function isUndercollateralized(address b) public view returns (ebool)

// ✅ Correct
function isUndercollateralized(address b) public returns (ebool)
```

---

## Gateway Callbacks — Always Use `onlyGateway`

```solidity
// ✅ Protected
function _onHealthCheckDecrypted(uint256 requestId, bool result)
    external onlyGateway { ... }

// ❌ Critical vulnerability
function _onHealthCheckDecrypted(uint256 requestId, bool result)
    external { ... }
```

---

## Gas Costs

| Operation | On-Chain Gas | Coprocessor Gas |
|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| FHE.add/sub | 8,000 | 65,000 |
| FHE.mul | 15,000 | 150,000 |
| FHE.div | 30,000 | 400,000 |
| FHE.lt/le/gt/ge/eq | 10,000 | 70,000 |
| FHE.select | 12,000 | 90,000 |
| FHE.asEuint64 | 6,000 | 50,000 |
| FHE.allow/allowThis | 3,000 | 0 |
| Gateway.requestDecryption | 25,000 | 200,000 |

Run `fhevm-forge gas` for a per-operation breakdown of your contracts.

