## Deploying

```bash
cp .env.example .env
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia --contract Counter
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia,base --contract Counter
fhevm-forge deploy --chains sepolia --contract Counter --dry-run
```

After deploying, update `frontend/app/contract.ts` with the new `CONTRACT_ADDRESS`.

---

## Common Errors and Fixes

| Error Code | Error | Cause | Fix |
|------------|-------|-------|-----|
| FHEVM-001 | State silently corrupted | Missing `FHE.allowThis()` | Call after every `euint` assignment |
| FHEVM-002 | External contract can't read handle | Missing `FHE.allow()` | Call `FHE.allow(handle, externalContract)` |
| FHEVM-003 | Function reverts unexpectedly | FHE op in `view` function | Remove `view` modifier |
| FHEVM-005 | Contract reverts on submit | Proof reused across contracts | Generate a new proof per contract |
| FHEVM-006 | Gateway callback callable by anyone | Missing `onlyGateway` | Add to all `_on*Decrypted` callbacks |
| FHEVM-007 | `abiEncodedClearValues` undefined | Wrong `publicDecrypt` destructuring | Use `{ results, clearValues }` |
| FHEVM-008 | `handles[N]` undefined | Index beyond getter return count | Use named destructuring |
| FHEVM-009 | `TFHE` / `SepoliaZamaFHEVMConfig` import errors | Old API used | Replace with `FHE` / `ZamaEthereumConfig` |
| FHEVM-010 | Wagmi rejects handle argument | `Uint8Array` passed directly | Convert: `` `0x${Buffer.from(handle).toString("hex")}` `` |

